Description. Male: Total length 2.76–3.01 ; male from Erlonghe Forest Farm, Jingyuan County (No. Ar- 2008 - 07245): body length 2.90 ; prosoma 1.43 long, 1.28 wide; opisthosoma 1.79 long, 1.17 wide. Carapace (
Fig. 1
) reddish brown, medially yellow. Carapace with long setae. Both eye rows recurved. Eye tubercles blackish brown with white rim. Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.10 , ALE 0.18 , PME 0.08 , PLE 0.13 ; AME–AME 0.18 , AME– ALE 0.13 , PME–PME 0.23 , PME–PLE 0.25 . MOA 0.38 long, anterior width 0.35 , posterior width 0.40 . Clypeus height 0.13 . Chelicerae yellow, promargin without teeth, retromargin with a denticle. Endites and labium yellow. Sternum heart-shaped, the front margin slightly recurved, the back end relatively acute. Legs yellowish and spinous. Leg measurements: I 4.89 ( 1.53 , 0.51 , 1.12 , 1.02 , 0.71 ); II 5.10 ( 1.58 , 0.51 , 1.28 , 1.02 , 0.71 ); III 3.32 ( 1.07 , 0.41 , 0.77 , 0.56 , 0.51 ); IV 3.72 ( 1.17 , 0.46 , 0.87 , 0.66 , 0.56 ). Leg formula: 2143 . Femora I–IV with two dorsal spines; femur I with three prolateral spines. Tibiae I –IV with two dorsal spines; tibiae I –II with two pairs of ventral, two prolateral, two retrolateral spines; tibiae III –IV with one ventral, one prolateral, one retrolaterla spine. Metatarsi I–IV with two prolateral, two retrolateral spines; metatarsi I –II with two pairs of ventral spines; metatarsi III –IV with one pairs of ventral spines. Opisthosoma nearly oval, cardiac pattern and muscular depressions visible; dorsum with a black brown markings; lateral sides with discontinuous white spots; venter grayish yellow.

Palpus (
Figs 5–7
). VTA digitiform, hooked apically; RTA wide, with tip biforcated, dorsal branch with two denticulations; tegulum flat, and sperm ducts round along the tegular margin; embolus thick and strong, bent.

